cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.SY, cs.DC 

This paper deals with security issues related to control-flow attacks and proposes a novel approach for detecting and preventing the execution of injected code and for mitigating code-reuse attacks such as return-oriented programming (RoP). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper involves dynamic binary instrumentation, which falls under the sub-category cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper also mentions the use of PIN, a dynamic program instrumentation framework from Intel, which is related to cs.PL (Programming Languages). The proposed approach is implemented for Windows x86, which is related to cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper involves benchmarks and evaluation, which are related to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
